values:
So I don't know if it actually counts as spring break, but I just finished my second trimester of school.  2 more weeks and then I start my Summer trimester (ewwwwwww school in the summer!)

I'm most excited about being able to sit down and read a book as my relaxation time and not feel guilty about not studying for some thing or another... I really wish I had a working xbox 360 though so I can finish playing my games :(

How is it that when I have time to study, I can't put my mind the state to study?  I have a microbio/immunology midterm on Thursday, and for the life of me I cannot concentrate enough to study for it.  I did badly on my herbs test today cause I didn't really study for it either.  :( :(  I think i'm in a funk or something...  not cool

So striwi died due to my lack of finances.  I guess it's ok, other than the fact that once striwi is gone I actually want to write in it.  Well, blogger is still around but it seems so pointless without striwi.  I was thinking that when I decide that finances are good enough that I can get striwi back, I might want to get a new domain name.  Striwi has been around since about 2005, and 5 years later, I feel like it's hard to part with.  It's like a pet that I don't want to give away even though I know I can't take care of it.

I think my new domain name (when I get it, that is) might be something related to acupuncture.  It seems like something that would fit, seeing that is the direction I'm heading towards.  I was thinking maybe calling it Du20 (Du20 is a point on the vertex of the head that is commonly used for memory) or some sort of play on words relating to acupuncture.  I guess I have a while to decide.  My other thought was to keep striwi as a domain, and get a separate domain for my acupuncture stuff.  I have no idea :(  I like the thought of keeping striwi sort of like an online portfolio of my arts and crafts... hmmmmmmm

Meanwhile, Livejournal, it's been a long time since I have written in you.  I guess this is the time to change, because, well, you're free.  I like that about you.  However I think I should change the layout, as this layout was done during a period of time I'd rather not remember, as pretty as I think the layout is.  It's been over 4 years and it's definitely time for a re-vamp.  Maybe that's my new project then.

Here's a present for you: FRANK, YOU'RE A MAJOR ASSHOLE.

This is me officially quitting.  And unlike all the other times I told myself I was going to give up, this time I mean it.  There's no point and I'm sick of being hurt over stupid things.  

You... are just not worth it anymore.

Starting after this post, all my future posts will be friends only.  Because I said so. So I had work between 1 and 6 today.  I think it was the first time I got everything done on time and I left only two minutes after 6.  Chris, Alex, and I went to Houlighans(sp?) for dinner.  That was amusing, our waiter must think Chris was a nutcase.  Chris apparently likes blu cheese... like, REALLY like it.  So with the appetizer came those little cups for dips and such, and one of them had blu cheese in it.  So we finished off the appetizers (...apparently, Alex hates mushrooms) and we're sitting around talking while Chris is dipping his fingers into the blu cheese and eating the cheese right off his finger.  The waiter comes, sees the empty dish, and goes, "Do you want me to take this away for you...." then he notices Chris's finger in it, and goes, "or do you want to leave it so you can dip in it some more...?"  Oh man, that was hilarious. Then later on, the waiter walks by as Chris was saying "genitalia... genitals!! genitalia... genitals!".  We later got ice cream and as we were done chris was playing in the ice cream with his spoon and the waiter was all "Geez, first the blu cheese now ice cream!?"  hahahahaha that was great. Chris is officially a Ross.  Alex: "You're definitely a Ross!" Jen: "you are SO Ross... you were just talking about dinosaurs" (ok so his dinosaur comment was about how this girl is ugly...) Chris: "Oh yea?? Well, if I'm Ross... then... You're Rachel!" Jen: "Am not!!!" Yea, that was interesting.  Friends were fun. Alex is officially shit-face-boy.  hahahahahahaha. Yea, dinner was very interesting.  Haha, hanging out with Chris & Alex is fun. -.- I have work at 7 in the morning.  tooo early. x.x

brought to you by Quizilla So today Mom, Kevin, and I went shopping. They were having crazy clearance sales over at Old Navy, so I managed to pick up a few shirts and two sets of bathing suits ($5 per peice, can you believe that? Normally, it's like $15 per peice! I was like, SWEET!). One has a hot pink camoflauge-ish design and the other is a cheetah pattern (haha my mom wanted me to get the cameo cause she thought the cheetah would make me look like a cavewoman e.e). Kevin got a few things too... And the grand total on the price? Less than $60 all together. We bought a WHOLE LOT of stuff. That's what I call a sale :) Then we went to Barnes & Nobles and I got kevin that double chocolate chip ice frappachino thing as a late part birthday present. I told him I'd get him a watergun tomorrow. I got the complete Vampire Chronicles of Anne Rice <3, I can't wait to start reading those, after the billion and one books I have on my to read list. I also got two Stephen King books, Hearts in Atlantis and Everything Eventual (14 Dark Tales) and Prey, which is a Micheal Critchon book. Whoop, the last three are all hardcover and they were on sale for all under $7 each. I was in bargain shopper heaven today :) And I also got a lamp for my desk (that you can paint the base, which is cool) and bookends. Now I just need to clean my room. Really. I keep saying I'll do it, but I never do. I'm lazy like that, but I'm tired of jumping around in my room just to get around without stepping on anything. Now I'm off to make a sign for my wonderful employers. Goodnight, you all.

Hmmm.  So today was fun.

I had work between 1 and 5, then I went home (obviously, hah).  Then Laura and I snuck off to the boardwalk, because her parents didn't want her to go to the boardwalk but she was allowed at my house.  Crazy.  Poor deprived boardwalk-virgin Laura is no longer a boardwalk-virgin.  

So we went to the boardwalk, and we looked for Vaanessaa.  We found her, and just as we were trying to talk to her, she made us go away because her boss was coming.  Hahaha that was really funny actually.  She's all "go away! go away! come back later! go!!"

So then we decided to walk around, and we met up with Joe Tirado.  Heh, wow, I haven't talked to Joe in a hell of a long time, and that was great.  He was showing us crazy magic tricks.  He's amazing actually.  Anyway we talked for about half an hour (he's really amusing) and then we decided to go hang out with Vaanessaa.  We went back, and to stay there I played the dart games.  Amazing, I actually won without killing any stuffed animals or castrating any famous cartoon character this time.  Whoop, I got a black and white bulldog.

So then we picked up Vaanessaa from her house and we went back to my house and we played tennis.  Mind you, it was after 9 and it was dark as anything.  It was really fun playing tennis without being able to see the ball.  You should try it sometime, really.  So then we sat on the court for a while to talk, and we decided to go back to my house and we went up to my room and I showed them the HUGE mess on the floor.  Then Laura and I started playing piano and guitar, and wow, Laura is amazing on piano.  So she started playing and I attempted to join in, and we ended up playing semi together, it was really awesome.  Maybe this week before she goes to the Governors School we can hang out again and do some song writing together.  It'd be awesome.

And I work all week except for Tuesday.  All at 7.  Hmm.
